3. System Architecture

3.1 High-Level Flow

User / AI Agent
→ Yellow Session Key
→ CompliFlow API
→ Policy Engine
→ Session-Key Preflight
→ Signed Compliance Receipt
→ Yellow Off-Chain Matching
→ Escrow
→ On-Chain Settlement

⸻

3.2 Architectural Components

3.2.1 Intent Gateway
Accepts structured TradeIntent objects containing:
	•	Session key identifier
	•	Wallet address
	•	Asset
	•	Amount
	•	Price
	•	Side
	•	Expiry
	•	Jurisdiction

All enforcement begins at intent evaluation.

⸻

3.2.2 Policy Engine
Deterministic rule engine that evaluates:
	•	Amount validation
	•	Price validation
	•	Side validation
	•	Jurisdiction restrictions
	•	Asset restrictions
	•	Allowance mirror constraints
	•	Session-key expiry buffers

Returns:
	•	PASS / FAIL
	•	Failure reason
	•	Structured decision payload

Rules are intentionally deterministic to avoid ambiguity.

⸻

3.2.3 Session-Key Preflight Module
Evaluates:
	•	Expiry thresholds
	•	Allowance alignment
	•	Revocation state (future extension)
	•	Risk heuristics

Preflight prevents:
	•	Execution using stale delegation
	•	Over-allowance execution
	•	Expired authority

⸻

3.2.4 Receipt Signer
All evaluations generate:
	•	Canonical payload
	•	Deterministic JSON representation
	•	Ed25519 signature

Receipt contains:
	•	Intent hash
	•	Decision
	•	Timestamp
	•	Version
	•	Signature

This enables:
	•	Auditability
	•	Replay detection
	•	External verification
	•	Proof-of-enforcement

⸻

3.2.5 Escrow-Aware Gating
CompliFlow can:
	•	Validate escrow state before match
	•	Validate escrow release conditions
	•	Attach compliance receipt to execution

This ensures enforcement precedes capital movement.

